sql:
SELECT year, mean_wage
FROM wage_history
WHERE occupation_id = 0 AND year > 2020;

SELECT occupation_id, employment_level
FROM employment_trends
ORDER BY employment_level DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "Janitors and Cleaners, Except Maids and Housekeeping Cleaners" refers to workers who clean buildings and maintain facilities;
- "Facilities Management" is an industry that deals with the maintenance and management of buildings and their systems;
- "BLS Survey 2023" is a data source from the Bureau of Labor Statistics, which provides detailed wage information.

- "average mean wage" refers to the mean wage calculated for each occupation, year, and quarter;
- "overall average" is the mean of all average mean wages across all occupations, years, and quarters;
- The results are ordered alphabetically by occupation name.

- "stands out like a diamond in the rough" means the occupation is exceptional and notable among its peers;
- "shines brighter" and "towers above" are metaphorical expressions indicating that the average wage and employment level of the occupation are higher than the overall averages;
- "presence in more than 10 establishments" implies that the occupation is widely available or represented.

sql:
SELECT AVG(mean_wage) AS average_wage
FROM wage_history
WHERE occupation_id = 1 AND year > 2020;

external_knowledge:
- "blossoming occupation" refers to an occupation that is growing and flourishing;
- "mean wage above the overall average" indicates that the occupation's average wage is higher than the average wage across all occupations;
- "thriving workforce" suggests that the occupation has a high employment level;
- "active employees" are employees who have not been terminated.

- 'flowers of occupation' refers to different occupations;
- 'bloom with an average mean wage' refers to the average mean wage for each occupation;
- 'stands taller than half the average height of all the flowers in the garden' refers to the condition where the average mean wage of an occupation is greater than half of the overall average mean wage.

- 'Growing' occupations refer to those with projected positive job growth;
- The dawn of the new decade refers to January 1, 2020;
- Historical wages are represented by the average wage from the wage history data.

- 'High School' refers to a typical education level that includes a high school diploma or equivalent;
- '1-3 years' refers to a typical experience level that ranges from one to three years of work experience;
- 'Mean wage' refers to the average wage for the occupation;
- 'Wage blossoms above $25,000' means the average wage is greater than $25,000;
- 'Garden of more than 100 employees' means there are more than 100 employees in the occupation.

sql:
SELECT AVG(wage) AS average_wage
FROM employees
WHERE occupation_id = (SELECT MAX(occupation_id) FROM occupations);
